William Jukes, Respondent, v. Amos R. Eno, Appellant. Decided May 6, 1889. Appeal from judgment entered upon verdict of jury, and from order denying *596motion for new trial, made upon the judge’s minutes. Thomas C. Ennever, for appellant. Wager & Acker, for respondent.

Before Sedgwick, Ch. J., and Freedman, J.

Per Curiam:

Judgment and order affirmed with costs.
